### Manage Playwright beforeEach and afterEach hooks globally for parameterized tests

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-parameterize-js.md

This example shows how to define `beforeEach` and `afterEach` hooks outside the `forEach` loop in Playwright parameterized tests. This ensures that the hooks run only once before and after all test iterations, which is suitable for setup/teardown that applies to the entire test suite.

```js
test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
  // ...
});

test.afterEach(async ({ page }) => {
  // ...
});

[
  { name: 'Alice', expected: 'Hello, Alice!' },
  { name: 'Bob', expected: 'Hello, Bob!' },
  { name: 'Charlie', expected: 'Hello, Charlie!' },
].forEach(({ name, expected }) => {
  test(`testing with ${name}`, async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto(`https://example.com/greet?name=${name}`);
    await expect(page.getByRole('heading')).toHaveText(expected);
  });
});
```

