This snippet from the documentation table illustrates how to set a specific timeout for `beforeAll` or `afterAll` hooks within Playwright using `test.setTimeout()`. This is crucial for hooks that perform lengthy setup or teardown operations, ensuring they have adequate time to complete without prematurely failing due to timeout.

