### Implement Playwright beforeAll Hook in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-test.md

Declares a `beforeAll` hook that runs once per worker process before all tests in its scope (file or `describe` group). It's used for setting up shared resources and can be paired with `test.afterAll` for teardown. The hook function is asynchronous and can accept an optional title.

```javascript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test.beforeAll(async () => {
  console.log('Before tests');
});

test.afterAll(async () => {
  console.log('After tests');
});

test('my test', async ({ page }) => {
  // ...
});
```

```javascript
test.beforeAll('Setup', async () => {
  console.log('Before tests');
});
```

