### Add Global beforeAll/afterAll Hooks via Worker Fixture (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-fixtures-js.md

Illustrates how to implement global `beforeAll` and `afterAll` hooks using auto fixtures with `scope: 'worker'`. These fixtures run once per worker process, providing setup before all tests in that worker and teardown after all tests complete. This is ideal for resource-intensive setup or cleanup that needs to occur only once per worker.

```typescript
import { test as base } from '@playwright/test';

export const test = base.extend<{}, { forEachWorker: void }>({
  forEachWorker: [async ({}, use) => {
    // This code runs before all the tests in the worker process.
    console.log(`Starting test worker ${test.info().workerIndex}`);
    await use();
    // This code runs after all the tests in the worker process.
    console.log(`Stopping test worker ${test.info().workerIndex}`);
  }, { scope: 'worker', auto: true }],  // automatically starts for every worker.
});
```

```typescript
import { test } from './fixtures';
import { expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('basic', async ({ }) => {
  // ...
});
```

