### Define Playwright beforeEach hooks per iteration in parameterized tests

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-parameterize-js.md

This snippet illustrates how to place `beforeEach` hooks inside a `test.describe()` block within a `forEach` loop for Playwright parameterized tests. This configuration ensures that the `beforeEach` hook executes for each individual test iteration, allowing for specific setup actions per parameterized test case.

```js
[
  { name: 'Alice', expected: 'Hello, Alice!' },
  { name: 'Bob', expected: 'Hello, Bob!' },
  { name: 'Charlie', expected: 'Hello, Charlie!' },
].forEach(({ name, expected }) => {
  test.describe(() => {
    test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
      await page.goto(`https://example.com/greet?name=${name}`);
    });
    test(`testing with ${expected}`, async ({ page }) => {
      await expect(page.getByRole('heading')).toHaveText(expected);
    });
  });
});
```

