### Conditionally Fixme a Playwright Test in a BeforeEach Hook

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-annotations-js.md

This example demonstrates using `test.fixme` within a `beforeEach` hook to conditionally mark tests as 'fixme' or skip them based on a condition, such as whether the test is running on a mobile device. This approach prevents subsequent logic within the `beforeEach` hook from executing for the marked tests.

```js
test.beforeEach(async ({ page, isMobile }) => {
  test.fixme(isMobile, 'Settings page does not work in mobile yet');

  await page.goto('http://localhost:3000/settings');
});

test('user profile', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.getByText('My Profile').click();
  // ...
});
```

