### Playwright API Test Setup and Teardown (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api-testing-js.md

This code demonstrates the use of `beforeAll` and `afterAll` hooks in Playwright tests to manage resources. It creates a new GitHub repository before all tests run and deletes it after all tests complete, ensuring a clean testing environment.

```javascript
test.beforeAll(async ({ request }) => {
  // Create a new repository
  const response = await request.post('/user/repos', {
    data: {
      name: REPO
    }
  });
  expect(response.ok()).toBeTruthy();
});

test.afterAll(async ({ request }) => {
  // Delete the repository
  const response = await request.delete(`/repos/${USER}/${REPO}`);
  expect(response.ok()).toBeTruthy();
});
```

