### Add Global beforeEach/afterEach Hooks via Auto Fixture (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-fixtures-js.md

Demonstrates how to implement global `beforeEach` and `afterEach` hooks using auto fixtures. By defining a fixture with `auto: true`, its setup code runs before each test, and its teardown code runs after each test, globally across all test files that import this fixture. This is useful for common setup like navigating to a base URL.

```typescript
import { test as base } from '@playwright/test';

export const test = base.extend<{ forEachTest: void }>({
  forEachTest: [async ({ page }, use) => {
    // This code runs before every test.
    await page.goto('http://localhost:8000');
    await use();
    // This code runs after every test.
    console.log('Last URL:', page.url());
  }, { auto: true }],  // automatically starts for every test.
});
```

```typescript
import { test } from './fixtures';
import { expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('basic', async ({ page }) => {
  expect(page).toHaveURL('http://localhost:8000');
  await page.goto('https://playwright.dev');
});
```

