### Implement Playwright afterEach Hook in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-test.md

Declares an `afterEach` hook that executes after each test, either globally in a file or within a `describe` group. It allows access to test fixtures like 'page' and the 'TestInfo' object, which can be used to log test status or page state after test completion. The hook function is asynchronous and can optionally be given a descriptive title.

```javascript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test.afterEach(async ({ page }) => {
  console.log(`Finished ${test.info().title} with status ${test.info().status}`);

  if (test.info().status !== test.info().expectedStatus)
    console.log(`Did not run as expected, ended up at ${page.url()}`);
});

test('my test', async ({ page }) => {
  // ...
});
```

```javascript
test.afterEach('Status check', async ({ page }) => {
  if (test.info().status !== test.info().expectedStatus)
    console.log(`Did not run as expected, ended up at ${page.url()}`);
});
```
